#, no-wrap
msgid "Exercise 3"
msgstr "Ejercicio 3"

#. type: delimited block =
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:242
msgid "In this exercise, you will publish an event dataset using the IPT."
msgstr "En este ejercicio, publicará un conjunto de datos de eventos utilizando el IPT."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:245
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/rubrics.adoc:94
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-birds-from-literature.adoc:148
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-herbarium-specimens.adoc:74
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-invasive-species.adoc:87
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-lepidoptera-sampling.adoc:99
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/use-case-marine.adoc:112
#, no-wrap
msgid "*Data publishing*\n"
msgstr "*Publicación de datos*\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:247
msgid "After cleaning the data in the dataset, the team considers that publishing the data online through GBIF could be a good way to make this effort visible. They plan on assigning the data with a CC0 waiver. You have been requested to lead that publishing work."
msgstr "Tras limpiar los datos del conjunto de datos, el equipo considera que publicarlos en línea a través de GBIF podría ser una buena manera de visibilizar este trabajo. Planean otorgar a los datos una de licencia de uso CC0. Se le ha solicitado que lidere este proceso de publicación."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:249
msgid "Download xref:attachment$UC-Practice-3-ForPublication.xlsx[UC-Practice-3-ForPublication.xlsx,opts=download]. (22 KB)"
msgstr "Descargar xref:attachment$UC-IS-3-ForPublication.xlsx[UC-IS-3-ForPublication.xlsx,opts=download]. (22 KB)"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:250
msgid "Open the file in Excel and export each tab as an individual CSV file (resulting in 4 files for upload to the IPT)."
msgstr "Abra el archivo en Excel y exporte cada pestaña como un archivo CSV individual (lo que dará como resultado 4 archivos para cargar en el IPT)."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:251
msgid "Use the assigned IPT installation to publish the dataset and register it with GBIF."
msgstr "Utilice la instalación IPT asignada para publicar el conjunto de datos y registrarlo en GBIF."

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:254
msgid "https://training-ipt-a.gbif.org/ \t"
msgstr "https://training-ipt-a.gbif.org/ \t"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:255
msgid "https://training-ipt-b.gbif.org/\t"
msgstr "https://training-ipt-b.gbif.org/\t"

#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:256
msgid "https://training-ipt-c.gbif.org/"
msgstr "https://training-ipt-c.gbif.org/"

#.  Note the lack of empty lines between the end of the question (....) and the start of the next question
#.  (. What…) is required, so I have added // comments to help separate them.
#.  The + connects the question into the numbered list item, see https://docs.asciidoctor.org/asciidoc/latest/lists/continuation/
#.  Question 1
#. type: delimited block *
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:273
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-publishing.adoc:239
msgid "What does data publishing mean in the context of GBIF?"
msgstr "¿Qué significa la publicación de datos en el contexto de GBIF?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:279
#: en/intro-to-gbif/modules/ROOT/pages/data-publishing.adoc:245
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [ ] Exporting a csv file of your cleaned data that you can share with your colleagues\n"
"- [ ] Writing an article describing your data, and the protocol(s) you used to collect, capture and clean them\n"
"- [x] Making your biodiversity dataset(s) publicly accessible and discoverable in a standardized format\n"
msgstr "- [ ] Exportar un archivo csv de sus datos limpios que puede compartir con sus colegas\n"
"- [ ] Escribir un artículo que describa sus datos, y el/los protocolo(s) que utilizó para recolectarlos, capturarlos y limpiarlos\n"
"- [x] Hacer públicamente accesibles sus datos de biodiversidad en un formato estandarizado\n"

#.  Question 2
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:282
msgid "What is an IPT?"
msgstr "¿Qué es un IPT?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:288
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [ ] a tool that helps you manage & correct your data\n"
"- [x] a tool that helps you publish your data to GBIF\n"
"- [x] a tool that helps you produce a Data paper\n"
msgstr "- [ ] una herramienta que lo ayuda a administrar y corregir sus datos\n"
"- [x] una herramienta que le ayuda a publicar sus datos en GBIF\n"
"- [x] una herramienta que le ayuda a producir una publicación de datos (Data Paper)\n"

#.  Question 3
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:291
msgid "Which Creative Commons licences and waivers are recommended by GBIF for data publication?"
msgstr "¿Qué licencias y exenciones de Creative Commons son recomendadas por GBIF para la publicación de datos?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:297
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [ ] CC-BY, CC-BY-SA and CC-BY-ND\n"
"- [x] CC0, CC-BY and CC-BY-NC\n"
"- [ ] CC0, CC-BY and CC-BY-SA\n"
msgstr "- [ ] CC-BY, CC-BY-SA y CC-BY-ND\n"
"- [x] CC0, CC-BY y CC-BY-NC\n"
"- [ ] CC0, CC-BY y CC-BY-SA\n"

#.  Question 4
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:300
msgid "What are the three Cores from which you can choose for an IPT resource?"
msgstr "¿Cuáles son los tres Núcleos (Cores) entre los que puedes elegir un recurso IPT?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:306
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [ ] Metadata Core, Occurrence Core, Multimedia Core\n"
"- [ ] Taxon Core, Collection Core, MeasurementOrFact Core\n"
"- [x] Occurrence Core, Taxon Core, Event Core\n"
msgstr "- [ ] Metadata Core, Occurrence Core, Multimedia Core\n"
"- [ ] Taxon Core, Collection Core, MeasurementOrFact Core\n"
"- [x] Occurrence Core, Taxon Core, Event Core\n"

#.  Question 5
#. type: Plain text
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:309
msgid "How many Extensions files can a dataset have?"
msgstr "¿Cuántos archivos de Extensiones puede tener un conjunto de datos?"

#. type: delimited block .
#: en/data-mobilization/modules/ROOT/pages/publishing.adoc:315
#, no-wrap
msgid "- [ ] zero\n"
"- [ ] one\n"
"- [x] as many as needed\n"
msgstr "- [ ] cero\n"
"- [ ] una\n"
"- [x] tantos como sea necesario\n"

